Text: Tough loss in Game 3, as Hawks fall 107-78 in Miami. ATL trails 2-1 in the best-of-seven series.
What I said earlier about Miami not shooting from 3 like they did in Game 2? Forget I said that...
75-61 Miami at the end of 3. Hawks not out of this, but need a strong start to the 4th to make it interesting. Come on #Hawks!
Of course.
Hmmm. We are quietly creeping up a lil bit...
A little run here to end the 3rd is all I want. I don't ask for much!
Mo Evans 3, and it's down to 14 at 66-52. Get some stops ATL! #Hawks
The offense is coming to life a bit more now, but we gotta get some stops.
A Wade turnover! What a bum! Am I right? Eh? Eh?
Good grief. Wade is on another planet right now.
Wow - tough lay-in for Mike Bibby there. Come on D!
Is is possible Jermaine O'Neal was hustling the NBA during the regular season?
Let's take it a little at a time. First let's get it down to 10 or so. Let's go #Hawks!
Tough end to the second quarter. Hawks trail 50-29 at the break. They've got their work cut out for them in the second half. #Hawks
Sigh. D-Wade is good.
Need a strong finish to this half. Down 40-29 with 2:49 to play. Let's go #Hawks!
Ok, what was more ridiculous - that 3 by James Jones, or Wade's bank job the other night?
After a 1-9 start for JJ, he's starting to hit his little runner in the lane. That usually bodes well for him. 31-25 Heat #Hawks
ATL has the A-Team Dancers. Miami has the "Jabba-OLD-eez". Pretty funny stuff
Of course, Miami isn't just going to give us the game - Heat 6-0 run makes it 31-23 MIA #Hawks
Josh Smith checks back in for Zaza - give it up for Big Z, he had a big impact in this comeback #Hawks
The tenor of this game has changed big time. It's on now. Horford with 2 straight buckets, and its 25-23 MIA #Hawks
Flip for 3! Watch out Miami, here we come! 22-19 MIA #Hawks!
The Heat seem to want to make it 100% certain that they won't hit 3's like they did the other night. Doesn't look like it so far.
I love the energy Zaza is providing right now. #Hawks
Hawks D starting to tighten up a bit, and JJ adds another basket on the other end. Let's keep it up #Hawks!
Nice strong move by Zaza to get a pair at the line.  22-14 MIA #Hawks
Moon hits a jumper at the buzzer and its 22-12 MIA at the end of 1. Gotta work on 6-25 shooting #Hawks
Ok, we are scoring some points now, I feel a bit better. JJ gets his first bucket. 20-12 #Hawks
And another for Flip - down to 8 #Hawks
Flip gets a steal and then a bucket. I have a feeling he could factor big tonight if we win... 18-8 #Hawks
Nice offensive rebound and bucket for Big Z. We need em where we can get em right now. 18-6 with 2:37 left in the first. #Hawks
Just gotta ride this out. 18-4 Miami in the first
Ouch. Wade jams and the Hawks call timeout. 13-4 MIA with 5:49 to play in the first.
@blaqbutterfli What I want to know is why were you checking out my attire???

Really?
Moon returns the favor. Wheew. Go #Hawks!

JJ to the line. Wade sat for a minute, but is set to come back in. #Hawks
Smoove answers Haslem. 96-91 with 4 to play! #Hawks
Wow. Huge bucket by Flip Murray with the and-1, and Wade gets his 5th in the process. My palms are getting sweaty. 94-89 #Hawks!
Looks like we're heading down to the wire. 93-86 MIA with 5:15 to play and the crowd is picking it up! Go #Hawks!

Wow. Charge on Wade. Great position there by Bibby. Gotta get this lead under 10!
The D continues to tighten the screws a bit, as Zaza draws the charge. Gotta get some buckets now! #Hawks
Way to go D out of the timeout, forcing the 24-second violation. Go #Hawks!
Bibby 3, and it's back to 10. I have a feeling we're going to need some more of those in the last 8 minutes. 93-83 MIA #Hawks
Trading points. 91-80 Miami @Hawks

Text: There's the playoffs we know.  A hard foul by Magloire, and Josh Smith stands up for his teammate with a little friendly shove. 89-78 Heat
Defense creates offense, Flip with the jam! 86-76. Go D!
BAM. Big three from Flip cuts the lead to 11 at the end of 3 as the crowd erupts! The Heat can't keep shooting this well from deep, I swear!
Steal and bucket by Flip, back to 14. The crowd is just dying for a Hawks run here. Let's go! #Hawks
1-2 at the line for Flip. Heat are really aggravating me with this whole "let's make every 3 we take tonight" thing #Hawks
Biiiiiiiiiiiig block by Smoove on Beasley. Come on D! #Hawks
Another whistle on the perimeter drawn by Wade. No comment... #Hawks
Flip checks in for Marvin, who has played very well tonight. With Joe out, we really need to "Flip the switch" #Hawks
Ugh. Wade again with the J - he is lights out tonight. Horford draws  3rd on JO on the other end but misses both. Too many missed FTs so far
3 on Wade. Would be nice to even him up with JJ.  Marvin has come alive as well in this half. 67-57 Miami #Hawks

Text: Timeout Miami as Bibby drains another jumper. He is heating up, and the Philips crowd erupts louder than they have all night. 65-55. #Hawks
Biiiiiiig play right there for ATL, maybe just the thing they need - Josh gets  a big block on Wade at one end, and Marv gets the and-1
Good grief. D-Wade has 5 threes in the game. Horford gets 2 of them back, and it's 65-50
And Bibby drains a jumper. Meanwhile, Jermaine O'Neal showing signs of life tonight for Miami #Hawks
JJ goes to the bench with his 4th foul. Hawks gotta respond without him for now.
Needed that three from Bibby in the worst way. Back to 60-46 Miami #Hawks
First half thoughts:  http://bit.ly/RRIXS
Blerg! Another Wade 3. We knew he'd come back in this game, and he has. Hawks gotta just stay calm and persevere.  54-41 MIA #Hawks
Another great pass from the perimeter by Josh Smith to Mo Evans for the jam :)
Oh boy. Wade is kinda on fire right now, he's scored 10 straight for Miami
I was just thinking we needed to get Big Al into the offense, and he gets a running hook. 45-37 MIA #Hawks
Hawks just can't seem to get untracked offensively. 10-point lead for Miami 45-35 #Hawks
I'll say this - Flip Murray has no fear going to the hole. His shot has been off so far in this series, but I like his aggressiveness #Hawks
Great defense by JJ on Wade forces the travel. This crowd is waiting for a Hawks run - come on ATL! #Hawks
3 threes from Cook for Miami. Gotta get out on him better. Cook fouls Josh on the other end, and the Hawks are in the bonus now. 39-33 MIA
@s_null21 I agree - I think generally speaking, the faster the game is played the more to the Hawks advantage #Hawks
Nice steal by Flip on Mike Beasley, and JJ draws the foul on Wade at the other end #Hawks
Chalmers 3rd foul, which is good. But it brings Wade back in the game, which is bad. I guess he was bound to return at some point though.
Boy, the Philips crowd loves them a Mike Bibby 3. The anticipation, the release as the ball drops through - it's pretty sweet. #Hawks
Daquean Cook is hot early for Miami with 2 3's, but Marvin answers with a drive on the other end. 32-25 Heat. #Hawks
Nice side pick n' roll by Bibby and Marvin gets Marv to the line for 2. Hawks still trail 29-23 #Hawks
JJ takes a rest with 8 points, tied for the team lead so far with Josh Smith
JJ rocks Jamario Moon to sleep on the bounce, then nestles in a jumper. 24-20 Miami
24-18 Miami at the end of one.  Hawks shooting 7-17 from the field, they'll need to improve on that as the game continues. #Hawks
I think the Heat should review the defensive 3-second rule during the next timeout. That's their third violation of the first quarter. # ...
A late call on Zaza Pachulia. The natives are getting restless with the officiating...
Beautiful drive and dish by Flip Murray to J-Smoove for the power jam. Smoove has 8 in the period.
The Hawks drew 3 fouls in the first 2 minutes, but somehow the Heat are the first into the bonus. 19-13 Miami #Hawks
2 quick touch fouls against Mo Evans guarding D-Wade. Grumble grumble grumble
D-Wade hits a 3, and it's 18-11 Miami. Yeah, methinks this game could be much closer tonight than Game 1
@scarlettotara He threw me off, that's for sure
2 straight buckets for Miami by JO, but Bibby answers with his first 3 of the game. 13-11 Miami
Timeout on the floor, and it's 9-8 Miami at the first official timeout. A sluggish first six minutes.
HIGHLIGHT! Marvin Williams blocks Haslem on one end, and JOE DUNKS THE BALL on the other. Joe! Dunk!
Smoove adds a jumper, 7-5 Miami. He's got 4
The Hawks are cold to start this game. Marvin and Bibby miss back to back 3's. Miami isn't shooting much better though
The Hawks are cold to start this game. Marvin and Bibby miss back to back 3's. Miami isn't shooting much better thought
And Spirit leaves to a rousing ovation. I'll be honest, I haven't seen the game the last few minutes. What's the score? Oh yeah, 5-3 Heat.
The spirit of Atlanta has shown up in full tonight at Philips Arena!
Jam. J-Smoove. Bam.
Wow - another offensive foul on Miami. Miami has 3 team fouls and we arent 3 minutes into the game
A few quick whistles against Miami - a defensive 3-sec, then fouls on Wade and Haslem. 2-1 Miami early
Once again, the Heat strike first, as they match their first half offensive rebounding total from Game 1 on a putback by Mario Chalmers

Both teams trading some ugly misses - let's go clock!
Big block by Josh Smith, and it's 82-70 with 4:30 left. A few more stops, and I'll start to feel a little more confident
My running commentary of the 3 Bibby just hit - "Shoot it! Wait a minute...wait a minute...Good."
@DBROWNJR11 Looking good right now - as long as the Hawks execute down the stretch, it's got the makings of a terrific home win.

Mo Evans with the breakaway jam! 72-58 Hawks at the end of the 3rd, and this place is going bananas!
Zaza with another offensive rebound and putback. You can't say enough right now about the effort of the Hawks bench.
And a foul on Jordan Farmar against Zaza Pachulia as well, for the extremely rare 4-point play with two players.
This third quarter belongs to Mo Evans. Another 3, and now he's got 11. 67-56 Hawks
The 3-point barrage continues - Mo Evans again! 58-48
Bam! 3 straight treys to start the second half, and the Hawks are back out to a 49-42 lead
Great way to start the 2nd half - Mo Evans for three!
Hawks lead 40-39 at the break. Both teams shot the ball relatively poorly in the first half - we'll see if that changes in the 2nd half
You knew the Lakers wouldn't go quietly - Kobe  3 cuts it to 38-37 Hawks
Wow - two straight buckets from Mario West, including a very, very impressive reverse lay-up. 38-27 Hawks with 3:42 left in the 2nd
Hawks hit a couple three by Bibby and Flip - 32-22 Hawks
Hawks D has been positively suffocating today
Zaza for MVP!

Flip vs Vujacic. Give Flip the ball
Josh Smith - missed dunk on a breakaway. I know it's a bad miss, but it was worth the risk - would have brought the house down.
Joe Johnson singing Billie Jean during the time-out - not quite in Josh Smith's league - probably needs to keep the day job.
Bibby J - Hawks take their first lead
Wow - Zaza Pachulia with max effort - Third time is the charm on the offensive glass for a basket. 10-10 with 3:43 left in the first

Terrell Owens back in the house today - and Ice Cube
